(Source: Bert Hubert's writings | Published: Sun, 16 Feb 2025 21:00:00 +0100) Tj
T*
(Link:) Tj
T*
(https://berthub.eu/articles/posts/a-brief-post-on-sqlite3-database-locked-despite-timeout/) Tj
T*
(So I?m a huge SQLite fanboy and I use it for almost everything these days. Recently, the) Tj
T*
(project added sqlite3_rsync which allows you to swiftly replicate your database to other) Tj
T*
(servers \(or to the same server if you want\), and this really was the cherry on top for me. Last) Tj
T*
(week however, I ran into one of my projects unexpectedly getting SQLITE_BUSY errors. And then) Tj
T*
(someone urged me to run ?a real database? \(PostgreSQL\), and that hurt.) Tj
